===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|cause|lang=enm}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|cause|lang=fro||a cause, a thing}} from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|causa||reason, sake, cause|lang=}}, in {{etyl|ML.}} also "a thing". Origin uncertain. See [[accuse]], [[excuse]]. Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[sake#Middle English|sake]]'' "cause, reason" (from {{ang}} ''[[sacu#Old English|sacu]]'' "cause"), {{enm}} ''[[andweorc#Middle English|andweorc, andwork]]'' "matter, cause" (from {{ang}} ''[[andweorc#Old English|andweorc]]'' "matter, thing, cause").

